cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves linear algebra and machine learning techniques, which are commonly found in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper's focus on word embeddings and their applications to IR suggests that it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper introduces a novel technique for dealing with polysemy, which could potentially fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
